SIMPLE: tripe
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tripe
<hw>Tripe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>tripe</ets>,
F. <ets>tripe</ets>; of uncertain origin; cf. Sp. & Pg.
<ets>tripa</ets>, It. <ets>trippa</ets>, OD. <ets>tripe</ets>, W.
<ets>tripa</ets>, Armor. <ets>stripen</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
large stomach of ruminating animals, when prepared for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How say you to a fat <qex>tripe</qex> finely broiled ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The entrails; hence, humorously or in contempt, the
belly; -- generally used in the plural.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tripedal</ent>⟦br⟧
